{
  "id": "fr_a1_lesson_010",
  "language": "fr",
  "level": "A1",
  "title": "Les nombres de 20 à 100 et l'argent",
  "description": "Master French's famously irregular counting system from 20 to 100, and use basic shopping/money vocabulary — vital for reading prices on any public sign.",
  "metadata": { "estimatedMinutes": 9, "xpReward": 50 },
  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "c1",
      "type": "TextCard",
      "title": "Les nombres de 20 à 100",
      "content": {
        "subtitle": "Module 5 · Leçon 1",
        "body": "French numbers get famously tricky between 70 and 99, where French switches to base-20 counting. Master this now, and prices, addresses, and phone numbers become effortless."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c2",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Les dizaines régulières",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "From 20 to 60, French numbers follow a simple, regular pattern — no surprises here.",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "vingt", "translation": "20" },
          { "text": "trente", "translation": "30" },
          { "text": "quarante", "translation": "40" },
          { "text": "cinquante", "translation": "50" },
          { "text": "soixante", "translation": "60" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 35 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "70 à 99 : le système base-20",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "This is the famous stumbling block: 70 is literally \"sixty-ten\", 80 is \"four-twenties\", and 90 is \"four-twenties-ten\". (Belgium and Switzerland use simpler regional forms, but standard French uses these.)",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "soixante-dix (60+10)", "translation": "70" },
          { "text": "soixante-quinze (60+15)", "translation": "75" },
          { "text": "quatre-vingts (4×20)", "translation": "80" },
          { "text": "quatre-vingt-cinq (4×20+5)", "translation": "85" },
          { "text": "quatre-vingt-dix (4×20+10)", "translation": "90" },
          { "text": "quatre-vingt-dix-neuf (4×20+19)", "translation": "99" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 45 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c4",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "cent",
        "nativeTranslation": "cent",
        "englishTranslation": "one hundred",
        "pronunciation": "sahn",
        "ipa": "sɑ̃",
        "partOfSpeech": "adjective",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "Ça coûte cent euros.",
        "nativeExample": "That costs one hundred euros.",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/cent.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c5",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "ça coûte / le prix",
        "nativeTranslation": "ça coûte / le prix",
        "englishTranslation": "that costs / the price",
        "pronunciation": "sah koot / luh pree",
        "ipa": "sa kut / lə pʁi",
        "partOfSpeech": "expression",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "Quel est le prix ? Ça coûte vingt euros.",
        "nativeExample": "What's the price? That costs twenty euros.",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/ca-coute.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c6",
      "type": "InfoCard",
      "title": "Lire les prix sur un panneau",
      "content": {
        "tone": "tip",
        "body": "TCF reading questions often show a photo of a price tag or public sign (\"Solde : -20%\", \"Ouvert de 9h à 19h\") and ask you to extract the number. Practice reading digits AND their French words together."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c7",
      "type": "FlashCard",
      "title": "Quick flip",
      "content": { "front": "cher / pas cher", "back": "expensive / cheap (not expensive)", "hint": "Tap to reveal the meaning" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 15 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c8",
      "type": "MultipleChoiceCard",
      "title": "Choisissez le bon nombre",
